---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../../components/TableOfContents.astro';

const headings = [
  { text: "TL;DR - Essential Care Tips", slug: "tldr" },
  { text: "Daily Maintenance", slug: "daily" },
  { text: "Washing & Conditioning", slug: "washing" },
  { text: "Heat Styling Guidelines", slug: "heat-styling" },
  { text: "Storage & Travel", slug: "storage" },
  { text: "When to Replace", slug: "replacement" }
];
---

<Layout 
  title="Complete Hair Extension Care and Maintenance Guide"
  description="Expert tips and techniques for maintaining your hair extensions. Learn proper washing, styling, and storage methods to extend their lifespan."
  image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1527799820374-dcf8d9d4a388?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80"
>
  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-24">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <img 
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1527799820374-dcf8d9d4a388?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80" 
        alt="Hair extension care"
        class="w-full h-96 object-cover rounded-lg mb-8"
      />
      
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-8">
        <time datetime="2024-04-05" class="text-gray-400">April 5, 2024</time>
        <div class="flex space-x-4">
          <button class="text-gray-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
            <span class="sr-only">Share on Twitter</span>
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M23.44 4.83c-.8.37-1.5.38-2.22.02.93-.56.98-.96 1.32-2.02-.88.52-1.86.9-2.9 1.1-.82-.88-2-1.43-3.3-1.43-2.5 0-4.55 2.04-4.55 4.54 0 .36.03.7.1 1.04-3.77-.2-7.12-2-9.36-4.75-.4.67-.6 1.45-.6 2.3 0 1.56.8 2.95 2 3.77-.74-.03-1.44-.23-2.05-.57v.06c0 2.2 1.56 4.03 3.64 4.44-.67.2-1.37.2-2.06.08.58 1.8 2.26 3.12 4.25 3.16C5.78 18.1 3.37 18.74 1 18.46c2 1.3 4.4 2.04 6.97 2.04 8.35 0 12.92-6.92 12.92-12.93 0-.2 0-.4-.02-.6.9-.63 1.96-1.22 2.56-2.14z"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <button class="text-gray-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
            <span class="sr-only">Share on Facebook</span>
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M18.77 7.46H14.5v-1.9c0-.9.6-1.1 1-1.1h3V.5h-4.33C10.24.5 9.5 3.44 9.5 5.32v2.15h-3v4h3v12h5v-12h3.85l.42-4z"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-playfair text-white mb-6">
        Hair Extension Care and Maintenance Guide
      </h1>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8 border border-gray-700">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-white" id="tldr">TL;DR - Essential Care Tips</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
          <li>üß¥ Use sulfate-free products specifically designed for extensions</li>
          <li>üöø Wash every 15-20 wears or when product buildup occurs</li>
          <li>üå°Ô∏è Always use heat protectant before styling</li>
          <li>üì¶ Store properly in dedicated extension storage cases</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:flex gap-12">
        <div class="lg:w-3/4">
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
            <h2 id="daily">Daily Maintenance</h2>
            <p>Proper daily care is essential for maintaining the quality and longevity of your hair extensions. Follow these daily maintenance tips:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Brush extensions 2-3 times daily using a loop brush</li>
              <li>Start from the bottom and work your way up</li>
              <li>Never brush wet extensions without a detangling spray</li>
              <li>Use a silk pillowcase to reduce friction</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="washing">Washing & Conditioning</h2>
            <p>Proper washing technique is crucial for maintaining your extensions:</p>

            <h3>Recommended Products:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Sulfate-free shampoo</li>
              <li>Alcohol-free conditioner</li>
              <li>Leave-in treatments for added protection</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Washing Steps:</h3>
            <ol>
              <li>Detangle thoroughly before washing</li>
              <li>Use lukewarm water</li>
              <li>Wash in a downward motion</li>
              <li>Never rub or twist the hair</li>
            </ol>

            <h2 id="heat-styling">Heat Styling Guidelines</h2>
            <p>While heat styling is possible with human hair extensions, proper precautions are necessary:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Always use heat protectant</li>
              <li>Keep temperature below 380¬∞F (193¬∞C)</li>
              <li>Style in small sections</li>
              <li>Avoid applying heat to attachment points</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="storage">Storage & Travel</h2>
            <p>Proper storage is key to maintaining your extensions' shape and quality:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Use dedicated extension hangers or storage cases</li>
              <li>Keep in a cool, dry place</li>
              <li>Avoid exposure to direct sunlight</li>
              <li>Never store wet extensions</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="replacement">When to Replace</h2>
            <p>Know when it's time to replace your extensions:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Significant tangling or matting</li>
              <li>Visible damage to the attachment points</li>
              <li>Loss of shine and natural movement</li>
              <li>Typically every 6-12 months with proper care</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="lg:w-1/4">
          <div class="sticky top-24">
            <TableOfContents headings={headings} />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>